********************************************************************
* DBA Minimizer                                                    *
* A tool set for minimizing deterministic Buechi automata          *
* (C) 2010/2011 by Ruediger Ehlers, Saarland University            *
********************************************************************

+-------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 0. Installation                                                   |
+-------------------------------------------------------------------+
After extracting the archive to a directory, run "make" in the
"Minimizer" directory. 

+-------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 1. History                                                        |
+-------------------------------------------------------------------+
- March, 26th, 2010: Initial release
- November, 10th, 2011: Bugfix - the "buechinizer" tool declared too
  many input Rabin automata as being unconvertable to deterministic
  Buechi automata. Also, now a simple minimization heuristic is
  applied by the "minimize.py" script prior to the SAT solving. This
  should typically lead to speed-ups in the overall minimization
  process.
- November, 25th, 2011: Bugfix in the minimization heuristic that
  is applied prior to SAT solving.

+-------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 2. Usage & Details                                                |
+-------------------------------------------------------------------+
Please gather the necessary information from the homepage of the
tool set: http://react.cs.uni-saarland.de/tools/dbaminimizer
